value.0: A heavy-set man with a dirty face, and large muscles from years of working in the mine.

Value.value: What'a ye think, then? Some frozen ale?
Cold coffee, warm beer! That's all we have here!
If'n you're cold, ye should head into the mines!

value.0: A heavy-set man with a dirty face, and large muscles from years of working in the mine.

Value.value: Cold out here, ja?
Don't get in the way o' my axe!
Good to get a fire going!

value.0: A heavy-set man with a dirty face, and large muscles from years of working in the mine.

Value.value: The ale's always frozen!
Without the fire, we wouldn't 'ave our ale!
Time to get back in the mines, soon.

value.0: A heavy-set man with a dirty face, and large muscles from years of working in the mine.

Value.value: Arharhar! Th' cart driver think I'm cookin' one o' 'is muskoxen!
Ain't but a bit o' lamb, is all...
It's cold here, but we have fire, and ale, and....muskox! Arharhar!

value.0: Not as bulky or strong as the miners around him, this cart driver brings ore and gear between the mine and the village.

Value.value: Damned miners, trying to eat my muskoxen!
Should hurry their arses up. I need to get the ore back before the storm hits!
Would but I had a coat like this! *pats the back of one of the muskoxen*

value.0: Not as bulky or strong as the miners around him, this cart driver brings ore and gear between the mine and the village.

Armor of this type began to appear in the lands adjacent to Thay in the Year of Smoldering Spells, 1020 DR. An irremovable coating of soot has blackened it, dulling noise of movement and making it ideal for stealthy endeavors. Close examination, however, reveals that the charring was not the result of externally applied heat, and suggests the original owner suffered some sort of Thayvian-induced combustion. This lends a very morbid feeling to the suit.
This magic bow has a bonus to attack. As well, it allows the wielder to add part of his strength modifier to the damage dealt.
A human in his later 40s. He has a taciturn and serious manner about him.
This is another outfit designed by Arwen E'lyn with a specific person in mind.  It is a dark clothing, designed to help cloak those who like to move in secrecy and shadow.
A fine silken suit from foreign lands woven with powerful protection magic for those that want to be stylish but not defenseless.
Piecemeal or complete armors of this grade are meager protection, no better than garments made of cloth or even rags.

Sewn from some of the finest silks on the island, this cloth is both beautiful, and durable. A set of gloves come with the cloth - a powerful arachnid-magic has been imbued in them to allow the wearer to shoot strands of silk at their foes.
Piecemeal or complete armors of this grade are meager protection, no better than garments made of cloth or even rags.

Another suit designed for the gentlemen by Arwen E'lyn, this suit is in tasteful browns.  It has Renaissance fashion in the sleeves to the wrist, fitted legs to the knee, and some fashionable, yet understated brown boots to the knee.
A simple, confident looking cloth. Wearing this, some may doubt the thought that you may actually kill them...
This is another outfit designed by Arwen E'lyn with a specific person in mind.  It is a dark clothing, designed to help cloak those who like to move in secrecy and shadow.
What better way to start your day than with a jaunty hat, replete with huge feather plume?  Boots, trousers, and flouffy shirt included, at no extra charge!
Clothes in browns and green for those who enjoy the great outdoors, by Arwen E'lyn.

A discreet loincloth for those wishing to wander about in a more natural state.  The lady's piece has a top on it (sorry, gents); Another Arwen E'lyn Design with a specific character in mind... Unlike many of Arwen's designs, this does not have the magical property of light; she figured a man in a loincloth did not need to be well lit....
Designed for those wishing to go without a shirt, this is just a pair of black trousers and boots.  For working, don't you know.  On hot days.

Monks of the Old Order do not worship any deity, but are devoted to the philosophy espoused by a deity who is either now dead or has never existed on the Material Plane of Toril.  The monks contradict themselves on this point, but the deity's identity isn't important to them, it's the message they care about.  The Old Order never has huge monasteries, but has spread widely throughout Faerun.  Monks of the Old Order generally are as well rogues, sorcerers and shadowdancers.  These robes contain small pockets in them that often contain either spell components, or other various necessities.
(The listed classes are the ones which monks of the Old Order may multiclass freely with in character, and would not receive the penalties given in pen and paper games)
True Robes of the Old Order
The Villainous Suit is slightly better than the Nimble Suit.  Having been designed by the same tailor, it has been given extra properties to aid in stealth and escape.
